:H2.ATTN
:XMP.
Format&gml. &gml.ATTN.attention name
:eXMP.
:I2 refid='gtattn'.gtattn
:P.
The optional attention tag is used to identify a specific person
or department at a general address.
The default text "Attention:\b" followed by the attention name text is placed
in the output document.
The attention tag must be specified after the :HP2.&gml.to:eHP2. tag.
The tags :HP2.&gml.attn:eHP2., :HP2.&gml.open:eHP2., and
:HP2.&gml.subject:eHP2. may be specified in any order.
